### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

Yes

### Description

I provide two **ng new --standalone=false** projects, one in Angular 19 and the other Angular 18.

In the develop build in Angular 19 forRoot will be called twice while in Angular 18 it will be called only once (see console.log output).

For production build both only call forRoot() once.

There is a console.log() in the forRoot() of the TestModule.


Is it a known consequence of the migration from angular 18 to 19 ?

See example code in the attachment.

