### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core

### Description

I would like to propose an idea that I had. To explain my issue first. If I had a component that used input but wanted to forward the input value to a service where the business logic is kept I had to use an effect api for that. Something like this:

```
@Component({
	selector: 'my-component'	
})
export class MyComponent {
	myService = inject(MyService);

	name = input<string>();

	private updated = effect(() => {
		const name = name();
		if (name) {
			this.myService.setName(name);
		}
	})
}


@Injectable()
export class MyService {
	private name = signal<string>();

	setName(name: string) {
		this.name.set(name);
	}
}
```

This looked quite boilerplatey to me so I had an idea if we could introduce something like a linkedInput where we could connect a service variable to a component input in a single line.

### Proposed solution

My proposition would be to add something like this:

```
@Component({
  selector: 'app-sample',
  template: `
    Hello {{ greeting() }}
  `,
  styles: ``,
})
export class SampleComponent {
  private service: SampleService = inject(SampleService);

  name = linkedInput<string>(this.service.name);
  greeting = this.service.greeting;

  constructor() {
    // Just to simulate input change
    this.name.set('John');
  }
}
```

which would directly set a signal in the service

```
@Injectable()
export class SampleService {
  name = signal<string>('');

  greeting = computed(() => {
    return `dear ${this.name()}`;
  });
}
```

A simple example of what I had in mind:
https://stackblitz.com/edit/stackblitz-starters-m1nfkxf6?file=src%2Fapp%2Fsample%2Fsample.component.ts

### Alternatives considered

No other alternatives so far

